    "en": "Simple conjunctions are used to connect sentences in German. At A1 level, the most basic conjunctions are taught.\n\n<strong>1. Und (and)</strong>\nConnects words or sentences.\nExample: Ich lerne Deutsch und spiele Fußball. (I learn German and play football.)\n\n<strong>2. Oder (or)</strong>\nOffers choices.\nExample: Willst du Tee oder Kaffee? (Do you want tea or coffee?)\n\n<strong>3. Aber (but)</strong>\nExpresses contrast.\nExample: Ich bin müde, aber ich arbeite. (I am tired but I work.)\n\n<strong>4. Denn (because)</strong>\nGives reason or explanation.\nExample: Ich gehe ins Bett, denn ich bin müde. (I go to bed because I am tired.)\n\n<strong>5. Verb Position</strong>\n- und, oder → verb stays in second position.\n- aber, denn → verb stays in second position.\n- These conjunctions do not form subordinate clauses.\n\n<strong>6. Summary</strong>\nSimple conjunctions are important to connect ideas in daily conversation.",
    
